16/12/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) arrested a Bosnian Muslim on Tuesday (December 15th), suspected of committing war crimes against Croat civilians and prisoners of war during the 1992-1995 Bosnian conflict. 
Jusuf Hadzajlija, 61, was detained in Konjic. 
He is suspected of having been a member of a Bosnian Muslim unit that attacked the village of Trusina, near Konjic, on April 16th 1993. 
(RTRS, Srna, Fena, BHRT, Dnevni Avaz - 15/12/09)
